page.title: 06Ecology two
page.content: Woods provide cover for numerous Red Deer,Badger,Fox.Hedge banks house Mice,Stoat,Vole,Hedgehog.Few hare. Rabbit population fluctuates with myxamatosis bouts.Moles & Squirrel can be a nuisance in field and garden.Var_ ious bat including Pippistrelle & Dau_ bentons.The streams and ponds support Brown Trout,Mallard & other duck, Coot Moorhen,Kingfisher,Mink,Heron from nearby heronery,also visitors Canada Geese,Cormorant,Common Sandpiper.Many Buzzard,Kestrel,Sparrow Hawk,occasion_ al Hen Harrier. Tawny & Little Owl, rare Barn Owl at West Tapps.Pheasant are common.Few Partridge,Snipe & Wood_ cock,rare Curlew.Common garden birds Blackbird,Robin,Wren,Song & Mistle Thrush,Finches & Warbles.Wood peckers green & Spotted.Visitors Swallow Swift & Martin.Plenty of dragonflies this year,fewer moths & butterflies.
